You can use the [Google Cloud client libraries](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/reference/libraries#use) to interact with your bucket in any of the supported languages.

If there isn't a client library for your language of choice, you can use the [JSON API](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api).

With both the client libraries and the JSON API, only blob/file/object APIs are authorized.

## Authorization

### Client libraries

1. Create a JSON file with these contents in your project root directory, \`google_application_credentials.json\`

\`\`\`
{
  "type": "external_account",
  "audience": "replit",
  "credential_source": {
    "url": "http://127.0.0.1:1106/credential"
  },
  "token_url": "http://127.0.0.1:1106/token"
}
\`\`\`

2. Set the \`GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS\` environment variable to \`"google_application_credentials.json"\`
3. Set the \`GCLOUD_PROJECT\` environment variable to \`""\`

### JSON API

1. Issue a \`POST\` request to \`http://127.0.0.1:1106/token\`

## Bucket Selection
Using Google Cloud APIs or libraries directly requires a bucket name parameter to be specified on all requests. This field is interchangeable with your bucket's ID within Replit App Storage.

To get the ID of the default bucket for your App or Deployment, issue a \`GET\` request to \`http://127.0.0.1:1106/object-storage/default-bucket\`
